Quiz 1: DDoS attacks, cybercrime, and underground economy

Q1: T/F: An attacker that uses large botnet to make requests to a server to flood is an example of amplification attack. 
Answer: True

Q2: T/F: Unlike UDP, TCP has the necessary safeguards in place to prevent network DoS.
Answer: False

Q3: Which of the following actors are part of the cyber crime underground economy? 
Answer: All of the above

Q4: Which of the following is/are NOT a potential network DoS mitigation? 
Answer: Use only TCP & Increase UDP 3-way handshake

Q5: In 2015, GitHub was a victim of a distributed denial of service attack. The attackers injected malicious JavaScript code in GitHub's web pages.
Answer: False
